Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.15,0:00:03.99,Default,,0,0,0,,We welcome all of you \Nto the December program \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.99,0:00:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,of JW Broadcasting!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.74,0:00:26.14,Default,,0,0,0,,This month \Nwe have something different \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.14,0:00:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,to share with you. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.44,0:00:29.21,Default,,0,0,0,,The Governing Body has decided \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.21,0:00:31.31,Default,,0,0,0,,that Gilead graduations\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.31,0:00:32.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and the spiritual portion \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.82,0:00:34.78,Default,,0,0,0,,of the annual meeting programs \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.78,0:00:40.42,Default,,0,0,0,,will be featured as monthly \NJW Broadcasting programs each year.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.42,0:00:43.86,Default,,0,0,0,,At this time, you will be able \Nto watch the first part \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.86,0:00:47.83,Default,,0,0,0,,of the graduation \Nof the 143rd class of Gilead. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.83,0:00:50.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You will enjoy listening \Nto the five Scriptural talks \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.93,0:00:52.94,Default,,0,0,0,,that will each be introduced to you \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.94,0:00:55.87,Default,,0,0,0,,by Brother Herd of the Governing Body.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.87,0:00:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Most languages \Nthat our monthly program is produced in \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.64,0:01:02.51,Default,,0,0,0,,did not have \Nthe resources to also translate \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.51,0:01:05.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and produce \Nthe Gilead graduation. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.35,0:01:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, by using the graduation \Nas the monthly program, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.75,0:01:12.89,Default,,0,0,0,,many more of our brothers and sisters \Naround the world \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.89,0:01:16.29,Default,,0,0,0,,will be able to enjoy \Nthis rich spiritual banquet.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.29,0:01:20.33,Default,,0,0,0,,We now invite you to enjoy \NPart One of the graduation \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.33,0:01:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,of the 143rd class of Gilead!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.84,0:01:28.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s graduation day \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.04,0:01:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,for this 143rd class of Gilead. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.24,0:01:35.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And it’s been a long time coming \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.38,0:01:39.25,Default,,0,0,0,,with a lot of work, worry, sweat, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.25,0:01:41.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and nerve-racking parts given \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.85,0:01:45.66,Default,,0,0,0,,in front of your instructors \Nand fellow classmates. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.66,0:01:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow! Ooh. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.39,0:01:53.10,Default,,0,0,0,,But none of you received \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.10,0:01:56.30,Default,,0,0,0,,a failing grade\N—not one. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.30,0:01:58.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re going to graduate today. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.30,0:02:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,This is your day. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.30,0:02:02.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And it’s a joyful day, isn’t it? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.87,0:02:06.44,Default,,0,0,0,,A very joyful day for you, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.44,0:02:10.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and a joyful day \Nfor each and every one of us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.75,0:02:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re glad you came to Gilead school, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.78,0:02:18.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and it saddens us a bit \Nto know you are leaving us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.79,0:02:21.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re not going to be here much longer. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.83,0:02:24.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Your fine spiritual instructors\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.56,0:02:27.13,Default,,0,0,0,,—Brothers Cauthon, Lippold, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.13,0:02:31.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Noumair, Samuelson, and Stovall\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.53,0:02:36.34,Default,,0,0,0,,—they would like to cry, \Nbut they’re good manly men, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.34,0:02:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and it’s hard for good manly men \Nto cry in public. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.88,0:02:45.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, there is a host of others\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.55,0:02:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,—too many to name—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.28,0:02:50.79,Default,,0,0,0,,such as Sam Herd. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.79,0:02:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Oops, it just slipped out \Nbeyond my control. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.59,0:02:58.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Your instructors have done \Na fine job of helping you \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.73,0:03:03.27,Default,,0,0,0,,to open your eyes \Nto see your “Grand Instructor” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.27,0:03:06.10,Default,,0,0,0,,mentioned at Isaiah 30:20. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.10,0:03:10.11,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, he is the one \Nwho has been teaching \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.11,0:03:12.68,Default,,0,0,0,,by giving his holy spirit \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.68,0:03:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to all these brothers that I’ve mentioned. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.31,0:03:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at what is stated at Isaiah 66:1\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.42,0:03:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,—66:1—it says: \N“This is what Jehovah says: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.46,0:03:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,‘The heavens are my throne, \Nand the earth is my footstool.’” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.73,0:03:37.07,Default,,0,0,0,,For the last five months, \Nyou’ve been sitting at Jehovah’s feet \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.07,0:03:41.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and you have been taught \Nby your Grand Instructor. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.27,0:03:45.71,Default,,0,0,0,,What you have learned \Nis much more than you knew \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.71,0:03:49.31,Default,,0,0,0,,when you first sat down five months ago. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.31,0:03:53.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Without a doubt, \Nthe knowledge you have taken in \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.25,0:03:56.99,Default,,0,0,0,,has brought you closer to Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.99,0:04:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You have really drawn close to Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.56,0:04:03.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and he has drawn close to you.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.99,0:04:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,However, you’ve only scratched the surface. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.47,0:04:11.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Job said: . . . \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.94,0:04:17.94,Default,,0,0,0,,[Indiscernible whispering]\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.94,0:04:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you hear what I said? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.04,0:04:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course you didn’t. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.05,0:04:26.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Now let’s read the scripture, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.78,0:04:29.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Job 26:14: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.39,0:04:32.99,Default,,0,0,0,,“Look! \NThese are just the fringes of his ways; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.99,0:04:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,only a faint whisper has been heard of him!” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.70,0:04:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,This is just about as much as we have learned \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.84,0:04:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,compared to what Jehovah knows. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.64,0:04:53.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Who knows all that Jehovah knows? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.54,0:04:56.45,Default,,0,0,0,,No one\N—not even Jesus, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.45,0:04:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and he knows quite a bit more than we do. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.95,0:05:05.15,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s been around longer, hasn’t he? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.15,0:05:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Much longer. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.16,0:05:10.53,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, Jesus was present \Nwhen the earth was created. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.53,0:05:12.66,Default,,0,0,0,,When was that? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.66,0:05:14.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if you’ve been listening \Nto morning worship, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.66,0:05:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,you’ll know that one member \Nof the Governing Body \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.80,0:05:18.97,Default,,0,0,0,,told us that in Proverbs chapter 8\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.97,0:05:20.37,Default,,0,0,0,,—he says take a look at that—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.37,0:05:25.01,Default,,0,0,0,,verses 29 and 30, and he read it to us, \Nhe said: “This is what it says.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.01,0:05:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,“When he established \Nthe foundations of the earth, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.64,0:05:31.65,Default,,0,0,0,,then I was beside him \Nas a master worker.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.65,0:05:33.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you remember that? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.65,0:05:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You don’t if you didn’t hear \Ntoday’s text or read it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.12,0:05:42.19,Default,,0,0,0,,But we are convinced \Nthat you heard it and you read it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.19,0:05:44.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that’s a long time, isn’t it? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.26,0:05:46.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The earth\N—foundations of the earth—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.53,0:05:48.53,Default,,0,0,0,,how long? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.53,0:05:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, based on the very old zircon rock \Nfrom Australia, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.64,0:05:55.74,Default,,0,0,0,,some scientists say we know that the earth \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.74,0:05:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,is at least four \Nand one-half billion years old, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.44,0:06:02.38,Default,,0,0,0,,give or take a hundred million years. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.38,0:06:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, no one really knows down here on earth, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.98,0:06:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,but we have to listen \Nto some of these so-called wise men. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.05,0:06:14.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus, in his prehuman existence, was there. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.76,0:06:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,There’s no doubt about that. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.76,0:06:19.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Colossians chapter 1 shows that, \Nthat he was there. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.73,0:06:24.03,Default,,0,0,0,,He was at Jehovah’s side way before then\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.03,0:06:25.77,Default,,0,0,0,,—listening and learning. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.77,0:06:27.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And he’s at Jehovah’s side today, isn’t he? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.87,0:06:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You know that. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.44,0:06:31.77,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s right there seated beside Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.77,0:06:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,doing the work that Jehovah \Nhas outlined that should be done.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.08,0:06:42.99,Default,,0,0,0,,When measured by Jesus, \Nwe’re newborn infants. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.99,0:06:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We barely have our eyes open, barely. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.19,0:06:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,What we see is not what we’re going to see \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.80,0:06:55.03,Default,,0,0,0,,in the years to come. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.03,0:06:57.77,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re just looking; we’re just learning; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.77,0:07:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,we’re touching things\N—and for the first time. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.00,0:07:04.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Just think, in the past ten years \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.67,0:07:07.81,Default,,0,0,0,,how many things \Nwe’ve touched for the first time. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.81,0:07:10.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though we’ve read the Bible \Nover and over again, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.18,0:07:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and we’ve listened to it \Nbeing read to us over and over again, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.88,0:07:17.62,Default,,0,0,0,,but we’ve just touched a few things\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.62,0:07:22.26,Default,,0,0,0,,—like the generation, \N20 years ago, the generation. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.26,0:07:25.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And now we know \Nall about that generation, right? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.50,0:07:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And so many other things\N—dragnet—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.70,0:07:32.70,Default,,0,0,0,,many other things, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.70,0:07:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,like the sanctification of God’s name, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.51,0:07:39.61,Default,,0,0,0,,vindication of his sovereignty\N—touch, touch, touch. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.61,0:07:42.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You Gilead students, \Nyou’ve touched a few things, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.25,0:07:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,but not everything, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.05,0:07:49.05,Default,,0,0,0,,not everything. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.05,0:07:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But what you have learned, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.59,0:07:57.66,Default,,0,0,0,,put to good use in your assignments. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.66,0:08:01.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep in mind that you don’t know it all. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.40,0:08:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And here’s something else: You never will. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.17,0:08:09.87,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter how long we live, \Nwe’ll never know it all. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.87,0:08:13.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah will still be revealing things to us, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.14,0:08:15.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and they’re always good things. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.95,0:08:19.72,Default,,0,0,0,,We benefit from what Jehovah gives us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.72,0:08:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,He knows exactly what we need, \Nand he gives it to us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.32,0:08:29.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So always keep that in mind. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.46,0:08:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re students under Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.50,0:08:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and that’s where we’ll always be. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.64,0:08:43.97,Default,,0,0,0,,But we’re happy. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.97,0:08:46.18,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re glad to be here. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.18,0:08:50.35,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re glad to be here with you students, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.35,0:08:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,every one of you, \Nand you’re good students too. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.15,0:08:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Now it’s true, not all of you \Nare A-plus students. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.32,0:09:04.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m not either. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.63,0:09:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I was happy to get a good C-plus in school.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.30,0:09:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we’re going to get started now \Nwith a major part of our meeting. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.87,0:09:21.21,Default,,0,0,0,,“Being Happy Despite Challenges” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.21,0:09:25.01,Default,,0,0,0,,is the theme of Brother Gerrit Lösch’s talk. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.01,0:09:27.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Lösch is a member \Nof the Governing Body. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.82,0:09:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,He is the senior member \Nof the Governing Body. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.46,0:09:36.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, I mean by that, \Nhe’s been a member of the Governing Body \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.39,0:09:39.06,Default,,0,0,0,,longer than the rest of us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.06,0:09:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m the oldest one on the Governing Body. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.33,0:09:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,We all face challenges of some sort. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.64,0:09:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So let’s listen carefully \Nto what he has to say, Brother Lösch.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.80,0:10:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“Oh happy day.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.17,0:10:21.04,Default,,0,0,0,,These are the first words of the gospel song. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.04,0:10:23.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And it goes on to say, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.04,0:10:28.04,Default,,0,0,0,,“Oh happy day, \Nwhen Jesus washed my sins away.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.04,0:10:30.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And we can agree \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.78,0:10:33.58,Default,,0,0,0,,with these music lyrics \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.58,0:10:36.42,Default,,0,0,0,,from the 18th century. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.42,0:10:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,We agree that forgiveness of sins \Nmakes us happy, doesn’t it? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.92,0:10:44.09,Default,,0,0,0,,But for many others, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.09,0:10:50.43,Default,,0,0,0,,the happy day is the payday \Nat the end of the month. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.43,0:10:53.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, what is a happy day for you students? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.77,0:10:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Graduation day. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.24,0:10:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,But you are not happy because it’s over, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.28,0:11:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,but because you had \Nthe privilege to attend Gilead. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.55,0:11:07.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Many in the world believe \Nthat if they had more money, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.82,0:11:09.82,Default,,0,0,0,,they would be happier. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.82,0:11:13.19,Default,,0,0,0,,However, many who made gaining of wealth \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.19,0:11:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the chief goal in life \Nnow suffer disappointment. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.76,0:11:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Some have lost their house, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.76,0:11:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,being unable to pay the mortgage \Nwhen they were laid off from work. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.20,0:11:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Wealth does not bring happiness. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.64,0:11:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Rather, lasting happiness \Ncomes from doing Jehovah’s will. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.41,0:11:33.41,Default,,0,0,0,,What is happiness? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.41,0:11:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Happiness is a state of well-being, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.08,0:11:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,contentment, even deep and intense joy. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.28,0:11:43.95,Default,,0,0,0,,But in the world, many are unhappy. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.95,0:11:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,In 2015, there were more than \Ntwice as many suicides \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.42,0:11:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,in the United States\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.56,0:11:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,—namely 44,193—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.46,0:11:59.54,Default,,0,0,0,,more than homicides, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.54,0:12:02.61,Default,,0,0,0,,where there were only 17,000 of those. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.61,0:12:06.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Up to 120 people take their life \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.44,0:12:09.71,Default,,0,0,0,,in the United States each day. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.71,0:12:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,How sad. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.45,0:12:15.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Though very rare, due to depression \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.75,0:12:18.42,Default,,0,0,0,,even some true Christians \Nhave taken their life, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.42,0:12:22.83,Default,,0,0,0,,but generally we are a happy people, \Naren’t we?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.83,0:12:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And here are 12 reasons for our happiness. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.00,0:12:31.73,Default,,0,0,0,,For one, we can be happy \Nbecause we worship a happy God. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.73,0:12:33.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Psalm 33:12: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.87,0:12:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“Happy is the nation whose God is Jehovah.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.91,0:12:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Secondly, because we have our sins forgiven, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.34,0:12:44.35,Default,,0,0,0,,as mentioned in the introduction. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.35,0:12:46.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Romans 4:7 says: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.35,0:12:49.15,Default,,0,0,0,,“Happy are those whose lawless deeds \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.15,0:12:54.49,Default,,0,0,0,,have been pardoned \Nand whose sins have been covered.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.49,0:12:56.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Number three, we can be happy \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.49,0:13:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,because we’re being loved \Nby Jehovah and Jesus. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.13,0:13:04.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Four, we’re happy because of being united \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.47,0:13:07.94,Default,,0,0,0,,with our worldwide brotherhood. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.94,0:13:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Five, we can be happy \Nbecause of living in a spiritual paradise, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.64,0:13:15.61,Default,,0,0,0,,having peace with Jehovah, \Nwith our brothers, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.61,0:13:19.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and also having plenty of spiritual food. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.98,0:13:22.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Six, in the Sermon on the Mount, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.69,0:13:25.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus emphasized spirituality when he said: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.69,0:13:30.19,Default,,0,0,0,,“Happy are those conscious \Nof their spiritual need.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.19,0:13:33.96,Default,,0,0,0,,In this sermon, he mentioned nine things \Nthat make us happy. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.96,0:13:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,What things? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.36,0:13:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you’ll find out \Nby rereading this sermon. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.10,0:13:43.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Number seven, we are happy \Nbecause our life has meaning, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.97,0:13:46.94,Default,,0,0,0,,namely, according to Ephesians 1:12, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.94,0:13:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to “serve for the praise of his glory.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.88,0:13:54.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Number eight, at Revelation 1:3, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.55,0:13:58.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus showed that \Nreading God’s Word makes us happy. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.29,0:14:03.03,Default,,0,0,0,,He says: \N“Happy is [he] who reads aloud \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.03,0:14:07.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and those who hear \Nthe words of this prophecy.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.46,0:14:10.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you want to be happy every day? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.10,0:14:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Read the Bible every day. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.17,0:14:18.17,Default,,0,0,0,,In the book of Revelation, \NJesus proclaims seven happinesses. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.17,0:14:19.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Which ones? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.91,0:14:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Find out by rereading Revelation. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.05,0:14:26.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Number nine, we are also happy \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.58,0:14:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,because we serve in the spiritual temple. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.52,0:14:32.25,Default,,0,0,0,,In Revelation 7, \Nnot just the anointed \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.25,0:14:35.79,Default,,0,0,0,,but also the great crowd \Nare shown serving, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.79,0:14:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,not near or before, \Nbut in the temple. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.60,0:14:43.63,Default,,0,0,0,,David called the Levites happy. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.63,0:14:45.70,Default,,0,0,0,,He said at Psalm 65:4:\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.70,0:14:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,“Happy is the one whom you choose \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.40,0:14:52.78,Default,,0,0,0,,[to] bring near to reside \Nin your courtyards.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.78,0:14:54.81,Default,,0,0,0,,David arranged the Levites \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.81,0:14:58.71,Default,,0,0,0,,so that they could serve at the temple \Ntwice a year for one week. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.71,0:15:01.95,Default,,0,0,0,,However, in contrast, \Nall of God’s people serve him \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.95,0:15:06.22,Default,,0,0,0,,in the spiritual temple all year long, \Nevery day. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.22,0:15:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,How happy we can be. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.76,0:15:12.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Number ten, Psalm 40:4 says: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.83,0:15:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“Happy is the man who trusts in Jehovah.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.47,0:15:21.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Trust is a must to maintain happiness. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.37,0:15:24.04,Default,,0,0,0,,When you arrive in your assignment, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.04,0:15:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,trust that Jehovah will support you. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.11,0:15:29.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Trust in Jehovah’s strength \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.48,0:15:33.35,Default,,0,0,0,,rather than in your Gilead training \Nand your abilities. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.35,0:15:37.65,Default,,0,0,0,,If low on funds, trust in Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.65,0:15:39.79,Default,,0,0,0,,He will care for you. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.79,0:15:44.33,Default,,0,0,0,,If you have to learn a new language, trust. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.33,0:15:47.86,Default,,0,0,0,,When you are being accused wrongly, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.86,0:15:51.73,Default,,0,0,0,,trust that matters will be clarified in time. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.73,0:15:56.17,Default,,0,0,0,,When you are discouraged, \Ntrust in better times. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.17,0:16:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,There is light at the end of each tunnel. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.71,0:16:04.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Number 11, we are happy \Nbecause we practice giving, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.71,0:16:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and Jesus said: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.48,0:16:10.99,Default,,0,0,0,,“There is more happiness in giving \Nthan there is in receiving.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.99,0:16:14.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Words well-known\N—Acts 20:35. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.99,0:16:19.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And 12, we are happy \Nbecause of the wonderful promise \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.66,0:16:22.13,Default,,0,0,0,,of a heavenly paradise for some \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.13,0:16:25.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and an earthly paradise for billions. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.23,0:16:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We are happy because this is tied \Nto the promise of everlasting life.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.11,0:16:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,How does happiness show? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.84,0:16:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It shows by a spirit of appreciation \Nand expressions of appreciation. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.55,0:16:43.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So beware of a complaining spirit. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.72,0:16:47.26,Default,,0,0,0,,When Jehovah liberated Israel, \Nthe people were happy. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.26,0:16:49.46,Default,,0,0,0,,However, within just a few weeks, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.46,0:16:54.90,Default,,0,0,0,,they complained and even wanted \Nto return to slavery in Egypt. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.90,0:16:58.23,Default,,0,0,0,,To stay happy, have a positive outlook. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.23,0:17:01.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t complain \Nabout the thorns on rosebushes, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.30,0:17:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,but be glad \Nthat some thornbushes have roses on it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.34,0:17:09.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Number two, when you go to your assignment, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.81,0:17:11.81,Default,,0,0,0,,radiate the happiness you feel. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.81,0:17:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Let others see it in your eyes, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.32,0:17:16.45,Default,,0,0,0,,in your face, in your smile; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.45,0:17:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,but smile, not like a salesperson, \Nbut smile from the heart. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.26,0:17:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Happiness is also shown by enjoying singing. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.26,0:17:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Happy people often sing. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.23,0:17:32.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Do we sing from time to time? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.87,0:17:34.87,Default,,0,0,0,,singing in the rain? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.87,0:17:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,or maybe in the shower? \Nor wherever? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.84,0:17:42.44,Default,,0,0,0,,How can we deepen our happiness? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.44,0:17:45.01,Default,,0,0,0,,What others do affects our happiness, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.01,0:17:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and what we do \Naffects the happiness of others. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.32,0:17:52.45,Default,,0,0,0,,We simply cannot escape \Nthe fact that our happiness \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.45,0:17:56.39,Default,,0,0,0,,is intertwined with the lives \Nof many other people\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.39,0:18:00.26,Default,,0,0,0,,—our families, our friends, and others. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.26,0:18:04.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Happiness is often in small things, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.27,0:18:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and unhappiness is the result \Nof neglecting small things. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.07,0:18:13.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Happiness is not the absence of challenges, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.51,0:18:17.05,Default,,0,0,0,,but the ability to overcome them. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.05,0:18:20.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Happiness does not depend \Non outside circumstances, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.58,0:18:22.58,Default,,0,0,0,,but on your inner thoughts \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.58,0:18:26.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and your relationship with our happy God. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.22,0:18:28.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Happiness is connected with joy, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.52,0:18:31.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and joy is part \Nof the fruitage of the spirit. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.03,0:18:33.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So avail yourself of the holy spirit, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.86,0:18:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and you will be happier.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.80,0:18:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You can be happy though hungry. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.50,0:18:42.30,Default,,0,0,0,,That was the title of a special talk. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.30,0:18:45.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, you can be happy \Nif you’re not hungry. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.64,0:18:48.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps you take advantage \Nof the “happy hour” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.84,0:18:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,in a restaurant where prices are reduced. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.88,0:18:56.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You can be happy though single. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.95,0:19:00.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You can be happy because of being married \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.02,0:19:03.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and sometimes despite being married. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.19,0:19:07.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You can be happy without children, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.43,0:19:11.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and you can be happy despite children. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.53,0:19:15.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You can be happy though \Nyou’re only 15 years old, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.17,0:19:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and you can be happy \Nalthough you’re 85 years of age. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.28,0:19:23.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You can be happy though you are sick \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.15,0:19:26.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and even more happy, \Nof course, if you’re healthy. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.01,0:19:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You can even be happy \Nthough you lost loved ones in death. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.42,0:19:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You will see them again. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.76,0:19:37.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You can be happy \Nthough persecuted for Christ’s sake. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.89,0:19:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus said at Luke 6:22, 23: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.63,0:19:43.73,Default,,0,0,0,,“Happy are you whenever men hate you . . . \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.73,0:19:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Rejoice in that day and leap for joy.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.67,0:19:52.27,Default,,0,0,0,,You can be happy if you lost your job. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.27,0:19:56.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You can be happy if you lost your wallet. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.38,0:19:59.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You can be happy if you lost your heart \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.55,0:20:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,in San Francisco\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.48,0:20:07.22,Default,,0,0,0,,—according to one song—\Nor somewhere else. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.22,0:20:11.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You cannot be happy if you lost your mind, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.19,0:20:13.70,Default,,0,0,0,,or maybe you can be even happier then \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.70,0:20:16.06,Default,,0,0,0,,because of not being aware \Nof all the problems \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.06,0:20:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,around you and affecting you. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.31,0:20:26.98,Default,,0,0,0,,If you are happy, you make others happy. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.98,0:20:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,If you are unhappy, you make others unhappy. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.21,0:20:33.25,Default,,0,0,0,,If you are not happy with others, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.25,0:20:36.29,Default,,0,0,0,,others will not be happy with you. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.29,0:20:39.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Humor adds to happiness. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.25,0:20:43.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It makes pain and problems more bearable. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.09,0:20:46.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Find happiness in small things\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.30,0:20:50.27,Default,,0,0,0,,—the sunset, the clouds in the sky, \Nthe birds chirping, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.27,0:20:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the butterfly on the flower, \Nthe dog chasing its tail. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.41,0:21:01.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Maintain happiness by meditating \Non the Paradise to come. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.01,0:21:03.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep it in expectation. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.01,0:21:05.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel 12:12 says: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.01,0:21:10.02,Default,,0,0,0,,“Happy is the one who keeps in expectation.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.02,0:21:14.06,Default,,0,0,0,,In Paradise, there will be no more tears,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.06,0:21:17.96,Default,,0,0,0,,no emotional pain, no unhappiness. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.96,0:21:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone will be happy every day, \Nall the time. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.56,0:21:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So let us maintain and deepen \Nour happiness despite challenges \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.57,0:21:30.11,Default,,0,0,0,,by praising our happy God, Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.11,0:21:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and making others and ourselves \Never more happy.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.72,0:21:51.83,Default,,0,0,0,,We certainly want to thank you, \NBrother Lösch. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.83,0:21:55.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You made all of us happy \Nwith that wonderful talk. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.83,0:21:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Our next speaker is Brother Gary Breaux, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.80,0:22:02.07,Default,,0,0,0,,a helper to the Service Committee \Nof the Governing Body \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.07,0:22:04.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and a Branch Committee member. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.21,0:22:05.91,Default,,0,0,0,,His theme is \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.91,0:22:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“Continue to Give Jehovah \NReasons Not to Forget.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.98,0:22:18.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we usually don’t think of Jehovah \Nas forgetting. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.79,0:22:22.46,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, he’s all-knowing, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.46,0:22:26.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and surely he doesn’t forget anything. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.06,0:22:28.63,Default,,0,0,0,,But you know, when it comes to humans, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.63,0:22:30.67,Default,,0,0,0,,it is possible to forget. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.67,0:22:33.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You remember the account in Deuteronomy. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.57,0:22:38.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Moses in this case \Nwas giving caution to the Israelites \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.11,0:22:41.61,Default,,0,0,0,,about life once they entered \Ninto the Promised Land. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.61,0:22:46.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And we have Deuteronomy 6:12, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.28,0:22:50.45,Default,,0,0,0,,he says: \N“Be careful not to forget Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.45,0:22:54.12,Default,,0,0,0,,who brought you out of the land of Egypt, \N[and] out of the house of slavery.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.12,0:22:58.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So it’s possible for servants of God \Nto forget Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.66,0:23:02.33,Default,,0,0,0,,But you know, \Nthat street goes both ways, so to speak. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.33,0:23:07.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The apostle Paul introduces the idea \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.34,0:23:10.47,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah God can forget too. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.47,0:23:16.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s at Hebrews 6:10. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.01,0:23:19.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Hebrews 6:10, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.41,0:23:22.75,Default,,0,0,0,,notice Jehovah’s ability to forget here, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.75,0:23:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,it says: “For God is not unrighteous \Nso as to forget your work \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.76,0:23:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,“and the love you showed for his name \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.26,0:23:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,by ministering and continuing to minister \Nto the holy ones.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.30,0:23:40.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So he says there are two things \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.34,0:23:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah God says \Nthat he will never forget. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.04,0:23:44.51,Default,,0,0,0,,What are they? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.51,0:23:48.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it’s work and love. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.38,0:23:52.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, remember the theme \Nof this talk that I chose. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.01,0:23:55.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s not “Give Jehovah Reasons Not to Forget” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.58,0:23:58.92,Default,,0,0,0,,because that would imply \Nthat you haven’t been doing that, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.92,0:24:01.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and that’s not the case. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.02,0:24:03.29,Default,,0,0,0,,But the theme is \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.29,0:24:08.70,Default,,0,0,0,,“Continue to Give Jehovah \NReasons Not to Forget.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.70,0:24:11.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And so it will be good for us \Nto look a little deeper \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.23,0:24:14.10,Default,,0,0,0,,into these simple words of Paul \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.10,0:24:18.97,Default,,0,0,0,,because it’s going to help us \Nnot to forget about Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.97,0:24:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And hopefully, he will not forget about us.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.48,0:24:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So we’re going to talk first about work, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.88,0:24:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and then we’ll come back and talk about love. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.28,0:24:32.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, it is interesting that Paul did not say \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.52,0:24:36.42,Default,,0,0,0,,that God would not forget your assignment. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.42,0:24:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah says: \N‘Oh, you’re a Branch Committee member. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.10,0:24:42.43,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Oh, I’ll never forget that. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.43,0:24:46.27,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Or you’re a pioneer; \Nyou’re a special pioneer; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.27,0:24:48.60,Default,,0,0,0,,‘you’re an elder. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.60,0:24:51.87,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Or you’re at a service desk \Nin a service department. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.87,0:24:53.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ll never forget that.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.58,0:24:56.51,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s not what Paul said in this verse. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.51,0:24:58.78,Default,,0,0,0,,What did he say? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.78,0:25:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,He said it’s the work \Nthat He will never forget. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.19,0:25:06.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, it’s true, \Nwe need Branch Committee members, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.42,0:25:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,we need elders, \Nwe need pioneers, and so forth. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.56,0:25:12.43,Default,,0,0,0,,But what Jehovah is not going to forget \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.43,0:25:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,is the work that we do \Nand the various assignments \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.30,0:25:18.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and the various ways \Nthat we serve Jehovah God, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.93,0:25:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,giving him whole-souled service.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.70,0:25:26.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I’d like to tell you about a brother \Nthat really understands \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.17,0:25:28.61,Default,,0,0,0,,this part of Hebrews 6:10 well. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.61,0:25:31.25,Default,,0,0,0,,A few years ago, we had five members \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.25,0:25:34.05,Default,,0,0,0,,on an Assembly Hall Committee \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.05,0:25:37.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and we were directed \Nto bring it down to three, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.15,0:25:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,so we had to remove two members \Nof every committee. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.92,0:25:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And the Branch Committee decided \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.76,0:25:44.69,Default,,0,0,0,,who was going to be removed \Nfrom the committee. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.69,0:25:46.29,Default,,0,0,0,,So the oldest brother\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.29,0:25:49.56,Default,,0,0,0,,—one of the oldest brothers serving \Nand age wise—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.56,0:25:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,it was decided \Nthat he would come off the committee. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.00,0:25:54.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So we had to send someone to tell him. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.04,0:25:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,We were not going to write a letter to him. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.24,0:25:59.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So guess what? \NI was chosen to go tell him. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.21,0:26:02.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So I was sitting at the table\N—conference table—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.01,0:26:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,with the Assembly Hall Committee, \Nand I was nervous, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.25,0:26:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and I was using the Scriptures, \Ntrying to get to their heart. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.42,0:26:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally, it got to the point \Nthat I had to say, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.52,0:26:12.75,Default,,0,0,0,,“Now, you two brothers \Nare being relieved of your assignment.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.75,0:26:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Immediately, \Nthe elderly brother raised his hand and said, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.26,0:26:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,“Can I read you a scripture?” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.56,0:26:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And I said, “Yeah, please do.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.20,0:26:24.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And he read Hebrews 6:10. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.43,0:26:28.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And he said: \N“Brothers, I’m here not for a title; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.90,0:26:30.91,Default,,0,0,0,,“I’m here to work. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.91,0:26:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Just give me work to do.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.14,0:26:38.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It affects me every time \NI tell that story because, really, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.11,0:26:41.85,Default,,0,0,0,,his comment captures what Paul is saying:\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.85,0:26:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Jehovah will not forget your work.’\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.82,0:26:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let’s go back to Hebrews 6:10 \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.76,0:26:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,because it talks about the second thing. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.96,0:26:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It says: \N‘He is not going to forget the love.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.70,0:26:59.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, what kind of love is he talking about? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.13,0:27:00.74,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Oh Jehovah, we love you.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.74,0:27:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah looks down: ‘Thank you very much. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.44,0:27:04.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ll never forget you love me.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.27,0:27:07.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that’s true, \Nbut that’s not what Paul is saying. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.91,0:27:10.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s read it again. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.15,0:27:13.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Verse 10, after he says \NHe won’t forget the work, he says: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.98,0:27:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,“And the love you showed for his name \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.12,0:27:22.66,Default,,0,0,0,,by ministering and continuing to minister \Nto the holy ones.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.66,0:27:25.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So there are a couple of words here \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.56,0:27:27.56,Default,,0,0,0,,that are important to understand. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.56,0:27:32.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s “you showed” and “ministering.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.67,0:27:36.74,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, \N‘Your love for your brother,’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.74,0:27:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah says, \N‘ah, look at that, I’ll never forget it.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.18,0:27:47.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, it’s not an intellectual love. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.88,0:27:50.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, you’ve been in class for what, \Nfive months? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.55,0:27:52.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I would imagine you’ve read every scripture; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.55,0:27:55.79,Default,,0,0,0,,you’ve heard all kinds of examples \Nabout showing love; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.79,0:27:59.83,Default,,0,0,0,,you have every reason to show love. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.83,0:28:03.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And now we encourage you: Go out and do it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.13,0:28:06.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Practice what you have learned. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.10,0:28:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember if it’s only words, \Nwhat did Paul say? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.50,0:28:12.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s like a cymbal\N—clashing cymbal. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.84,0:28:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So love means action; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.24,0:28:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,it doesn’t just mean words.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.58,0:28:25.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I’d like to tell you another little story \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.05,0:28:29.02,Default,,0,0,0,,about a brother that had \Nsomewhat of a difficulty with this. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.02,0:28:31.43,Default,,0,0,0,,When I was a young circuit overseer, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.43,0:28:36.23,Default,,0,0,0,,the district overseer I had was—\NI was afraid of him. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.23,0:28:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody else was scared of him too. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.00,0:28:43.81,Default,,0,0,0,,At one circuit assembly, \Nhis wife wasn’t there, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.81,0:28:48.58,Default,,0,0,0,,so he didn’t tell anybody \Nwhy she wasn’t there, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.58,0:28:50.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and we’d never ask. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.78,0:28:53.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And so anyway, \Nthe closing talk on Sunday, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.31,0:28:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I decided, \Nwithout getting his permission, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.92,0:28:57.99,Default,,0,0,0,,to let everyone know what was going on. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.99,0:29:01.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And I said: “Now you notice \Nthat his wife isn’t with him. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.49,0:29:05.73,Default,,0,0,0,,“I just wanted you to know that tomorrow \Nshe’s going to have a major operation, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.73,0:29:09.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and so we should all keep them \Nin our prayers, OK?” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.46,0:29:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Then they introduced him. \NHe didn’t come out. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.33,0:29:17.24,Default,,0,0,0,,He was back behind the stage \Nand for a long time. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.24,0:29:19.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn’t know what to do, frankly. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.37,0:29:22.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Soon, this man comes out \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.01,0:29:24.81,Default,,0,0,0,,very, very slowly, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.81,0:29:28.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and he gets to the microphone; \Nhis voice is cracking. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.05,0:29:30.08,Default,,0,0,0,,He starts talking a little bit, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.08,0:29:33.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and he gives his whole talk \Nin this very low tone. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.39,0:29:35.39,Default,,0,0,0,,At the end of the program, you know, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.39,0:29:38.93,Default,,0,0,0,,we always have this heartwarming song. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.93,0:29:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Then he had to pray. \NHe couldn’t pray. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.36,0:29:44.60,Default,,0,0,0,,He started crying. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.60,0:29:48.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally, after a long time, \Nhe said a word or two, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.37,0:29:49.94,Default,,0,0,0,,“In Jesus’ name, Amen.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.94,0:29:52.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what happened next? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.74,0:29:54.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The circuit surrounded him. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.98,0:29:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,They were hugging him. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.88,0:29:59.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody was crying. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.18,0:30:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,He told me later, he said: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.22,0:30:04.52,Default,,0,0,0,,“Gary, I love the brothers. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.52,0:30:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I just don’t know how to show it.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.53,0:30:13.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Now if you relate to that experience, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.43,0:30:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,learn how to show love.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.00,0:30:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, what can you do? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.00,0:30:21.37,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, it might be a need \Nto change your face. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.37,0:30:25.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, not your face, but have a softer face. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.64,0:30:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe you need to soften your voice. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.25,0:30:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe you need to develop \Na more inviting personality. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.58,0:30:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Do things for people; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.19,0:30:44.26,Default,,0,0,0,,take care of the old brothers and sisters \Nin the congregations you’re going to be with. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.26,0:30:48.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if it’s not natural for you \Nand you feel awkward about it, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.06,0:30:53.07,Default,,0,0,0,,do it anyway because in time \Nit will become part of you. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.07,0:30:57.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Because when you walk in that front door \Nof your Kingdom Hall \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.24,0:31:00.01,Default,,0,0,0,,or the front door of your branch, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.01,0:31:02.91,Default,,0,0,0,,the brothers should be drawn to you, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.91,0:31:06.28,Default,,0,0,0,,not because of your assignment, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.28,0:31:11.99,Default,,0,0,0,,but because you have worked hard \Nto show love. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.99,0:31:14.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So as you go to your assignments, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.09,0:31:17.99,Default,,0,0,0,,always remember that Jehovah knows \Nthe work you have done \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.99,0:31:20.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and the love you have shown, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.19,0:31:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and he will never forget it.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.68,0:31:42.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much, Brother Breaux, \Nand we’ll keep those reasons in mind \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.18,0:31:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,if we don’t forget. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.06,0:31:51.09,Default,,0,0,0,,“Who am I, O Jehovah God?” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.09,0:31:53.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know who asked that question? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.53,0:31:55.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I don’t. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.53,0:31:58.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So let’s give our attention \Nto Brother Patrick LaFranca, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.50,0:32:01.67,Default,,0,0,0,,a helper to the Personnel Committee \Nof the Governing Body \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.67,0:32:04.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and a member of the Branch Committee. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.04,0:32:07.31,Default,,0,0,0,,He will give us the answer.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.31,0:32:09.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Gilead students, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.61,0:32:12.98,Default,,0,0,0,,have you ever asked yourself, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.98,0:32:18.89,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Who am I to have been invited \Nto Gilead school?’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.89,0:32:21.39,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s a good question, isn’t it? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.39,0:32:23.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Because very few of God’s people, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.63,0:32:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,relatively speaking, have had that privilege. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.86,0:32:29.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So why you? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.70,0:32:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Was it because you were \Nsmarter or better looking \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.23,0:32:35.54,Default,,0,0,0,,than the average servant of Jehovah? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.54,0:32:40.54,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it was \Nbecause of your spiritual qualities. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.54,0:32:45.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And foremost among those was humility. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.55,0:32:48.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You have been humble. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.25,0:32:51.89,Default,,0,0,0,,But maintaining humility \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.89,0:32:54.59,Default,,0,0,0,,is a definite spiritual challenge\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.59,0:32:57.79,Default,,0,0,0,,—not just for you but for all of us, really. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.79,0:33:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ve all inherited the tendency \Nto exalt ourselves. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.76,0:33:04.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You think of Adam and Eve. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.57,0:33:09.17,Default,,0,0,0,,In the act of profound arrogance, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.17,0:33:12.57,Default,,0,0,0,,they wanted to put themselves in God’s place. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.57,0:33:15.41,Default,,0,0,0,,They seemed to forget who they were\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.41,0:33:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,—creatures made of dust. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.15,0:33:24.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So we all have to fight \Nagainst prideful tendencies. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.59,0:33:27.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Humility is elusive. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.32,0:33:31.43,Default,,0,0,0,,As soon as we think we are humble, \Nwe’ve lost it.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.43,0:33:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,However, Jehovah gives us help. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.63,0:33:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,In the Bible, there are many examples \Nof those who did maintain humility, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.27,0:33:41.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and one of these is David. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.54,0:33:45.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s just follow David’s life a bit\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.81,0:33:50.55,Default,,0,0,0,,—different stages of his life—\Nand see, did he maintain humility? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.55,0:33:54.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, was he humble as a young man? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.52,0:33:59.29,Default,,0,0,0,,You remember how Jehovah \Ndirected the prophet Samuel \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.29,0:34:03.26,Default,,0,0,0,,to go to Jesse’s house \Nand annoint one of Jesse’s sons \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.26,0:34:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,as the future king of Israel.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.16,0:34:10.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, seven of his sons were there, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.43,0:34:13.30,Default,,0,0,0,,but not one of them was chosen. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.30,0:34:17.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And finally, Samuel said,\N‘Are these all your sons?’\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.77,0:34:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,‘No, there’s David out in the fields \Nshepherding the sheep.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.01,0:34:25.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So they called David, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.18,0:34:28.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and Samuel anoints this young man \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.95,0:34:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to be the future king of Israel. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.45,0:34:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,David must have been surprised \Nat this singular privilege that he had. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.03,0:34:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, did he become high-minded? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.17,0:34:47.27,Default,,0,0,0,,How would he have treated his brothers\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.27,0:34:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,—his older brothers—\Nhad he become prideful? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.14,0:34:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, he could have said to Eliab: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.98,0:34:59.55,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Well, I guess you got taken down \Na peg or two, didn’t you? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.55,0:35:02.45,Default,,0,0,0,,‘You better start respecting me. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.45,0:35:05.09,Default,,0,0,0,,‘And Abinadab, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.09,0:35:08.92,Default,,0,0,0,,‘isn’t it time for you to go out now \Nand shepherd the sheep? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.92,0:35:11.69,Default,,0,0,0,,‘I have a more important assignment. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.69,0:35:14.20,Default,,0,0,0,,‘I have to learn to be king. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.20,0:35:18.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm, how can I get into the king’s court?’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.33,0:35:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,No, nothing indicates \Nthat David felt that way about himself. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.04,0:35:28.01,Default,,0,0,0,,He was content to wait on Jehovah \Nfor future privileges.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.01,0:35:30.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there a lesson here for us? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.98,0:35:34.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, you may get future privileges, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.22,0:35:36.38,Default,,0,0,0,,but you may have to wait for them. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.38,0:35:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Go back to your pastures; \Nshepherd the sheep. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.02,0:35:44.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So after some time, \NDavid is still in the pastures, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.43,0:35:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and what happens? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.96,0:35:48.30,Default,,0,0,0,,An attendant of King Saul \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.30,0:35:52.97,Default,,0,0,0,,recommends that David serve \Nin the king’s court. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.97,0:35:55.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen to this recommendation \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.07,0:35:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,at 1 Samuel 16:18: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.24,0:36:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,“One of the attendants said: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.25,0:36:09.25,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Look! I have seen\Nhow a son of Jesse the Bethlehemite\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.25,0:36:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘plays skillfully, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.59,0:36:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘and he is a courageous, mighty warrior. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.16,0:36:17.16,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘He can speak well, and he is handsome, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.16,0:36:20.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and Jehovah is with him.’” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.13,0:36:23.97,Default,,0,0,0,,My, what an impressive recommendation! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.97,0:36:27.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So, humble David goes from the sheepfold \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.77,0:36:31.71,Default,,0,0,0,,to the king’s court as a court musician. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.71,0:36:33.54,Default,,0,0,0,,But more privileges followed. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.54,0:36:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You’ll see in verse 21b \Nthat he became Saul’s armor bearer. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.38,0:36:43.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And later, David had many exploits in war. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.25,0:36:45.25,Default,,0,0,0,,He became famous. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.25,0:36:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Women sang about his victories. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.92,0:36:51.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So fame, good looks, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.66,0:36:53.66,Default,,0,0,0,,youth, eloquence, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.66,0:36:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,musical skills, \Nmilitary prowess, divine favor\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.20,0:36:59.50,Default,,0,0,0,,—David had it all, didn’t he? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.50,0:37:04.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And any one of those things \Ncould have made him arrogant and prideful, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.01,0:37:07.54,Default,,0,0,0,,but it seems that they did not. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.54,0:37:10.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Note David’s reaction when King Saul \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.38,0:37:14.22,Default,,0,0,0,,offered David his daughter in marriage. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.22,0:37:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That is at 1 Samuel 18:18: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.39,0:37:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,“At this David said to Saul: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.19,0:37:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Who am I and who are my relatives, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.23,0:37:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘my father’s family in Israel, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.26,0:37:32.67,Default,,0,0,0,,for me to become son-in-law to the king?’” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.67,0:37:35.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, being related to the king \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.57,0:37:38.21,Default,,0,0,0,,might have given David reason to boast, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.21,0:37:43.14,Default,,0,0,0,,but his words “who am I” resonate with us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.14,0:37:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,David felt unworthy \Nof being related to the king.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.32,0:37:50.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there any lesson, perhaps, in this for us? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.85,0:37:53.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we may work with and come into contact \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.45,0:37:57.83,Default,,0,0,0,,with prominent brothers \Nin God’s organization. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.83,0:38:02.43,Default,,0,0,0,,In conversations with others, \Ndo we drop their names, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.43,0:38:07.57,Default,,0,0,0,,trying to make ourselves,\Nperhaps, seem more important?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.57,0:38:12.51,Default,,0,0,0,,But now we come \Nto another period in David’s life. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.51,0:38:16.71,Default,,0,0,0,,He is now the king of Israel \Nwith his capital in Jerusalem, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.71,0:38:20.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and he’s dwelling in a royal palace. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.18,0:38:24.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And he’s being—\NHe’s feeling very embarrassed \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.49,0:38:29.02,Default,,0,0,0,,because here he is in a royal palace \Nand the ark of Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.02,0:38:33.13,Default,,0,0,0,,who is the real king of Israel, \Nis in a tent. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.13,0:38:37.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And so he says to the prophet Nathan, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.57,0:38:42.27,Default,,0,0,0,,‘I want to build Jehovah a worthy house\N—a temple.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.27,0:38:45.07,Default,,0,0,0,,But Jehovah says, \N‘No, not you, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.07,0:38:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,but one of your sons will do that.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.44,0:38:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,However, then Jehovah did something \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.68,0:38:56.35,Default,,0,0,0,,that took David completely by surprise. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.35,0:39:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,God tells him, \N‘Instead of you building me a house, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.22,0:39:04.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I am going to build a house for you.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.76,0:39:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And he makes a covenant with David \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.36,0:39:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,so that the kingship would remain \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.16,0:39:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,in the family line of David forever. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.14,0:39:18.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, how did David react? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.37,0:39:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Please open to 1 Chronicles 17:16-18: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.21,0:39:30.18,Default,,0,0,0,,“At that King David came in \Nand sat down before Jehovah and said: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.18,0:39:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Who am I, O Jehovah God? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.52,0:39:37.79,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘And what is my house \Nthat you have brought me this far? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.79,0:39:40.29,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘As if this were not enough, O God, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.29,0:39:43.16,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘you also speak \Nabout the house of your servant \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.16,0:39:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘down to a distant future time, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.67,0:39:49.14,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘and you have looked on me \Nas if I were a man \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.14,0:39:52.61,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘who should be further exalted, \NO Jehovah God. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.61,0:39:56.14,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘What more can your servant David say to you \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.14,0:39:58.21,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘about the honor given me \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.21,0:40:02.25,Default,,0,0,0,,when you know your servant so well?’” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.25,0:40:04.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So this marvelous promise \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.62,0:40:08.12,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah made to David touches his heart, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.12,0:40:12.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and he sits before Jehovah in humility, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.79,0:40:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,feeling so unworthy and insignificant. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.40,0:40:21.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And later, David made \Nan enormous contribution \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.57,0:40:23.67,Default,,0,0,0,,for the building of the temple \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.67,0:40:25.67,Default,,0,0,0,,that by today’s standards \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.67,0:40:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,would amount to over 1,200,000,000 dollars. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.11,0:40:34.08,Default,,0,0,0,,But in prayer to Jehovah, he says, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.08,0:40:37.38,Default,,0,0,0,,as recorded at 1 Chronicles 29:14: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.38,0:40:40.99,Default,,0,0,0,,“And yet, who am I . . . \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.99,0:40:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,“For everything is from you, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.12,0:40:48.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and what we have given to you \Ncomes from your own hand.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.16,0:40:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,What a humble spirit. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.16,0:40:52.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And it’s true, isn’t it? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.17,0:40:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever we give to Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.20,0:40:58.54,Default,,0,0,0,,it’s something \Nthat he has already given to us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.54,0:41:03.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s no wonder that Jehovah God loved David. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.11,0:41:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,He was a man really agreeable \Nto God’s own heart.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.92,0:41:12.92,Default,,0,0,0,,How can we cultivate and maintain \Nsuch a humble heart? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.92,0:41:15.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s not simply by saying, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.32,0:41:17.73,Default,,0,0,0,,“I am determined to be humble.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.73,0:41:21.23,Default,,0,0,0,,No, but do as David did. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.23,0:41:25.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Once in a while, sit down, \Ntake a long look at your life, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.87,0:41:30.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and see what blessings, \Nwhat undeserved kindnesses, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.50,0:41:33.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah has extended to you. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.17,0:41:36.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Ponder over his awesomeness. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.24,0:41:40.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And when we do so, \Nwe will be moved to say to Jehovah: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.58,0:41:44.32,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Who am I, Jehovah God, \Nthat you’ve honored me, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.32,0:41:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,‘making me one of your fellow workers \Ndespite my many flaws? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.32,0:41:51.33,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Who am I, Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.33,0:41:54.30,Default,,0,0,0,,‘that you’ve given me health and strength \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.30,0:41:57.13,Default,,0,0,0,,‘to serve in my assignment? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.13,0:42:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Who am I, O God, \Nto have this special privilege of service \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.07,0:42:05.24,Default,,0,0,0,,when I know there are many more \Nand more deserving than I?’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.24,0:42:09.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, there is a wholesome pride \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.21,0:42:12.28,Default,,0,0,0,,in having the privilege \Nof being one of God’s servants, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.28,0:42:15.38,Default,,0,0,0,,but it is an unhealthy pride \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.38,0:42:17.82,Default,,0,0,0,,that makes one feel superior. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.82,0:42:20.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And if we are looking down on others, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.02,0:42:23.09,Default,,0,0,0,,we cannot be looking up at Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.09,0:42:27.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And that really is the secret \Nof maintaining humility\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.70,0:42:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,—to know what we really are. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.46,0:42:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,We always keep Jehovah before us \Nas David did. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.47,0:42:38.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So students, we have every confidence \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.61,0:42:42.14,Default,,0,0,0,,that you will keep your eyes \Non your awesome God, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.14,0:42:45.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and that he will use you\Nand he will bless you\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.55,0:42:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,even more than he has\Non this day of your graduation.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.73,0:43:07.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I don’t know about you, \Nbut I was enlightened \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.87,0:43:10.50,Default,,0,0,0,,by “Who Am I, O Jehovah God?” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.50,0:43:13.77,Default,,0,0,0,,That was David that said that. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.77,0:43:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, live and learn. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.88,0:43:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother James Cauthon, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.88,0:43:21.05,Default,,0,0,0,,one of our Theocratic Schools instructors, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.05,0:43:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,will speak on the theme \N“Sympathetic Strings.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.29,0:43:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Imagine that you had the means \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.16,0:43:33.39,Default,,0,0,0,,to give everyone in your life \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:33.39,0:43:35.40,Default,,0,0,0,,an expensive gift. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.40,0:43:37.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what would happen? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:37.40,0:43:39.40,Default,,0,0,0,,They would be happy. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.40,0:43:42.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You would be happier \Nbecause you would experience \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.87,0:43:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,what Jesus said is a greater happiness\N—giving. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.11,0:43:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, you can give others \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.98,0:43:54.42,Default,,0,0,0,,something that is very special\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.42,0:43:58.89,Default,,0,0,0,,—something they really need—\Nand it won’t cost you a cent. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.89,0:44:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.89,0:44:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s your attention. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.96,0:44:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Romans 12:15, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.36,0:44:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,the apostle Paul wrote this, he said: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.30,0:44:15.74,Default,,0,0,0,,“Rejoice with those who rejoice; \Nweep with those who weep.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:15.74,0:44:20.31,Default,,0,0,0,,We need to learn to understand \Nand share another person’s feelings \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.31,0:44:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,whether it’s joy or sadness. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.38,0:44:24.38,Default,,0,0,0,,But why? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.38,0:44:25.71,Default,,0,0,0,,We need to understand it \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.71,0:44:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,because we’re living \Nin “critical times hard to deal with.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.28,0:44:33.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And so when the Bible says \Nto “weep with those who weep,” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.75,0:44:36.02,Default,,0,0,0,,we can sum that up in two words: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.02,0:44:38.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Show sympathy.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.06,0:44:40.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Why should we do that? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:40.23,0:44:45.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, going back to Romans 12, \Nand this time in verse 5, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:45.23,0:44:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,notice what we’re reminded of. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:49.37,0:44:54.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Paul wrote: “So we, although many, \Nare one body in union with Christ, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.41,0:44:59.21,Default,,0,0,0,,but individually we are members \Nbelonging to one another.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.21,0:45:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Now this, of course, was written \Nwith those of the new covenant in mind, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.22,0:45:07.82,Default,,0,0,0,,but in reality all of us as Jehovah’s people \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.82,0:45:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,belong to one another. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.96,0:45:14.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, you might find it interesting to know \Nthat in the Christian Greek Scriptures, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.63,0:45:18.97,Default,,0,0,0,,there are some 50 “one another” commands:\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.97,0:45:22.60,Default,,0,0,0,, Love one another, encourage one another, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.60,0:45:27.47,Default,,0,0,0,,incite one another, \Npray for one another, and other things.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.47,0:45:30.21,Default,,0,0,0,,The Watchtower said this, it said:\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.21,0:45:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,“We should be sensitive to the pains \Nand heartaches of our brothers and sisters. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:34.72,0:45:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,“Often, we can bring much relief \Nto fellow believers \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.75,0:45:39.82,Default,,0,0,0,,“who are suffering emotional pain \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.82,0:45:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,“if we take the time to listen to them \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.06,0:45:45.93,Default,,0,0,0,,with a truly sympathetic ear.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.93,0:45:49.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Sympathy is entering in \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.33,0:45:52.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and sharing in the pain of others. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.37,0:45:55.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, sometimes in English we say “empathy.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.57,0:46:00.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s also translated “fellow feeling” \Nor even “feel pity.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:00.01,0:46:03.71,Default,,0,0,0,,But it’s in times of crisis, grief, \Nand doubt \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.71,0:46:06.38,Default,,0,0,0,,when we need one another the most. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.38,0:46:09.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So how can we show that we care? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.22,0:46:13.95,Default,,0,0,0,,The answer is simple: Listen sympathetically.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.95,0:46:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The effect can be likened \Nto the sympathetic strings that are used \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:18.59,0:46:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to enhance the sound and harmony \Nof certain musical instruments. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:31.00,0:46:36.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, all of these have strings \Nthat are not played, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.01,0:46:39.55,Default,,0,0,0,,but they react \Nto the strings that are struck \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.55,0:46:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,or plucked, if you would, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:42.28,0:46:45.09,Default,,0,0,0,,thus they become sympathetic.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.09,0:46:47.49,Default,,0,0,0,,They produce a unique harmony. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:47.49,0:46:49.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s a oneness, really. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:49.49,0:46:51.49,Default,,0,0,0,,The effect of this \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.49,0:46:55.30,Default,,0,0,0,,is something that is very special. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.30,0:46:59.37,Default,,0,0,0,,But now, how this actually works \Ncan be demonstrated with the use \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.37,0:47:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,of two tuning forks. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:03.04,0:47:07.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Notice the one reacts to being struck. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.17,0:47:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The second, although not being struck, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.88,0:47:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,reacts to the feelings of the first. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:14.48,0:47:17.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So the first fork is no longer alone. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.58,0:47:20.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It has become joined by a second fork \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.75,0:47:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,that is now also picking up the vibrations \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:23.92,0:47:26.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and is said to be sympathetic. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.59,0:47:28.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s a harmony, really. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:28.83,0:47:33.10,Default,,0,0,0,,After the loss of a loved one, \None sister said: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.10,0:47:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,“Tears became the language of my heart. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.84,0:47:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I so appreciated it when the friends \Ncame over and just cried with me.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.44,0:47:45.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure, it’s a oneness\N—a harmony. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.91,0:47:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,She felt it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.92,0:47:51.59,Default,,0,0,0,,We recognize, though, \Nthat there is a certain caution here \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.59,0:47:55.02,Default,,0,0,0,,because sharing joy is one thing, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:55.02,0:47:59.19,Default,,0,0,0,,but sympathetically listening \Nto another’s pain of heart \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.19,0:48:01.19,Default,,0,0,0,,can be emotionally taxing\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:01.19,0:48:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and time-consuming.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.67,0:48:11.67,Default,,0,0,0,,As our illustration demonstrates, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:11.67,0:48:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,even after the original fork is removed, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.84,0:48:17.54,Default,,0,0,0,,the sympathetic one \Nis still feeling the effects, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:17.54,0:48:19.55,Default,,0,0,0,,isn’t that right? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:19.55,0:48:22.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And that’s why, \Nwhether we like it or not, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.58,0:48:25.75,Default,,0,0,0,,our actions will reveal \Nwhat’s really in our hearts \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:25.75,0:48:28.79,Default,,0,0,0,,when it comes to our brothers and sisters.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.79,0:48:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Going back to Romans again, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:31.06,0:48:35.13,Default,,0,0,0,,this time Romans 12:10,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.13,0:48:37.40,Default,,0,0,0,,we’re reminded of this. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.40,0:48:43.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It says: “In brotherly love \Nhave tender affection for one another.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:43.37,0:48:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Listening is a simple gesture of affection. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:47.84,0:48:52.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Often the problem, of course, \Nis that we’re in such a hurry to fix things \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.55,0:48:55.25,Default,,0,0,0,,that we feel that we can’t take the time \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:55.25,0:48:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,to listen to someone else \Nor to sympathize with them. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:59.42,0:49:03.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Or sometimes we’re so preoccupied \Nwith our own hurts \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:03.72,0:49:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,that we’re caught up in that. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.96,0:49:11.80,Default,,0,0,0,,But self-pity will smother sympathy \Nfor others. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.80,0:49:14.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And we need to be careful, frankly, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.37,0:49:16.70,Default,,0,0,0,,because sometimes we feel \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:16.70,0:49:18.91,Default,,0,0,0,,that we just have to solve \Nthe problem right away, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:18.91,0:49:21.27,Default,,0,0,0,,so we make statements \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:21.27,0:49:25.81,Default,,0,0,0,,that are not helpful \Nto the person that is suffering. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:25.81,0:49:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,‘You know, you need to just toughen up.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:30.62,0:49:33.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Or here’s one of my favorites: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.99,0:49:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Others suffered, now it’s your turn.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.06,0:49:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Or comparisons: \N‘Well, at least you can walk.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.27,0:49:49.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we don’t mean those things \Nto be malicious, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.70,0:49:51.87,Default,,0,0,0,,but how do they come across? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:51.87,0:49:55.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, they come across as condescending. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:55.54,0:49:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And it’s another way of saying, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.28,0:50:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,“I don’t care” or “I don’t care enough.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.92,0:50:07.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Job tried ten times \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.29,0:50:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,to explain to his comforters his feelings. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:10.32,0:50:13.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And finally, after the tenth time, he said, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.09,0:50:16.60,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Oh, if someone would but listen to me.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:16.60,0:50:19.23,Default,,0,0,0,,His hurt, his pain, was enhanced \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.23,0:50:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,because of his companions’ failure to listen. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.44,0:50:25.61,Default,,0,0,0,,How sad that is. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:25.61,0:50:28.21,Default,,0,0,0,,They neither cared about Job, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:28.21,0:50:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,nor did they want to understand his feelings. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.82,0:50:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,They shut him down.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.12,0:50:45.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Could we ever do \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:45.19,0:50:47.56,Default,,0,0,0,,the same thing or something similar? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:47.56,0:50:50.20,Default,,0,0,0,,How sad that would be.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:50.20,0:50:55.10,Default,,0,0,0,,To share in someone’s grief and pain, \Nyou must be willing to listen, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:55.10,0:50:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,you must be willing to take the time, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:57.10,0:51:00.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and you must care more about them \Nthan you do yourself. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:00.14,0:51:04.34,Default,,0,0,0,,We need to learn to take ourself \Nout of the equation. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:04.34,0:51:07.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Romans 12:10 continues: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:07.08,0:51:10.95,Default,,0,0,0,,“In showing honor to one another, \Ntake the lead.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:10.95,0:51:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,We honor others by being nonjudgmental, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:14.42,0:51:16.52,Default,,0,0,0,,by taking them seriously, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:16.52,0:51:20.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and by giving sincere heartfelt attention \Nand consideration \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.63,0:51:23.70,Default,,0,0,0,,to their words and their feelings. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:23.70,0:51:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,We need to remember this point: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:27.67,0:51:31.47,Default,,0,0,0,,That is, that our relationship with God \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:31.47,0:51:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and our relationship with our brothers \Nis one and the same. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:37.18,0:51:39.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me repeat that. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.25,0:51:41.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Our relationship with God \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:41.35,0:51:45.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and our relationship with our brothers \Nis one and the same. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:45.55,0:51:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah cares deeply \Nabout how we interact with one another. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.16,0:51:54.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah wants his people to be known \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:54.83,0:51:58.67,Default,,0,0,0,,for their love for one another \Nmore than anything else. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.67,0:52:00.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So your gift \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:00.67,0:52:02.67,Default,,0,0,0,,of sympathetic concern \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:02.67,0:52:05.14,Default,,0,0,0,,will be a powerful means of showing love \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:05.14,0:52:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and restoring a measure of harmony \Ninto the lives of others.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:29.20,0:52:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,With talks like that, \NI can see why I’m not one of the instructors. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.60,0:52:39.21,Default,,0,0,0,,The illustration of the two forks \Njust drove the point home, didn’t it? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.21,0:52:41.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, here’s another, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:41.51,0:52:46.51,Default,,0,0,0,,“The Glowing Coal” is the theme \NBrother Mark Noumair has chosen. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.51,0:52:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s also one \Nof the Theocratic Schools instructors \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.28,0:52:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and a helper to the Teaching Committee \Nof the Governing Body. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:53.15,0:52:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Noumair, \Nwe are burning with anticipation.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:59.39,0:53:02.43,Default,,0,0,0,,On joyous occasions as today, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:02.43,0:53:07.03,Default,,0,0,0,,your love burns strong, and rightly so. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:07.03,0:53:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember this day. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:09.04,0:53:13.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Etch indelibly in your minds \Nhow you feel right now \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:13.37,0:53:17.14,Default,,0,0,0,,because this love \Nthat is burning brightly within you \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:17.14,0:53:20.98,Default,,0,0,0,,will be tested. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:20.98,0:53:23.32,Default,,0,0,0,,When we undergo trials, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:23.32,0:53:27.05,Default,,0,0,0,,reviewing Bible accounts \Nof faithful men and women \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:27.05,0:53:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,can bolster our own faith. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:29.42,0:53:34.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And we can hear their words \Nringing in our minds. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:34.43,0:53:38.50,Default,,0,0,0,,But what about those \Nwho have never spoken a word \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:38.50,0:53:41.37,Default,,0,0,0,,recorded in the Bible? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:41.37,0:53:46.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Can their silent examples of faith help us?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:46.37,0:53:48.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s consider one. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:48.38,0:53:50.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Her name is Rizpah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:50.94,0:53:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,We know very little about her. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:53.15,0:53:56.95,Default,,0,0,0,,She is first introduced to us \Nas a concubine of King Saul. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.95,0:54:01.96,Default,,0,0,0,,No doubt, she must have been very beautiful \Nto catch the attention of the king. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:01.96,0:54:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,However, her life was not an easy one. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:05.76,0:54:07.29,Default,,0,0,0,,In time, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:07.29,0:54:09.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Saul\N—the father of her children—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:09.13,0:54:10.66,Default,,0,0,0,,is killed in battle. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:10.66,0:54:14.17,Default,,0,0,0,,She now becomes the property \Nof Saul’s son, Ishbosheth. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.17,0:54:16.54,Default,,0,0,0,,He too is killed.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:16.54,0:54:20.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Unfortunately, Rizpah’s most painful test \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:20.94,0:54:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,was yet to come. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:24.61,0:54:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Long after Saul’s death, \NJehovah tells King David \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:28.15,0:54:31.15,Default,,0,0,0,,that bloodguilt remains on Saul’s house \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:31.15,0:54:35.19,Default,,0,0,0,,because of his attempt \Nto annihilate the Gibeonites, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:35.19,0:54:38.22,Default,,0,0,0,,which violated an ancient covenant. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:38.22,0:54:42.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Thus, the entire nation of Israel is guilty \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:42.73,0:54:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,of shedding innocent blood. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:45.80,0:54:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,How does David resolve this issue? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:48.40,0:54:52.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Second Samuel 21:3 \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:52.57,0:54:54.94,Default,,0,0,0,,shows what David did. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.94,0:54:59.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Second Samuel 21:3, \NDavid asks the Gibeonites: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:59.55,0:55:02.02,Default,,0,0,0,,“What should I do for you?” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:02.02,0:55:04.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Verse 6, they answer: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:04.58,0:55:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,“Let seven of [Saul’s] sons be given to us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:08.15,0:55:11.39,Default,,0,0,0,,We will hang their dead bodies \Nbefore Jehovah.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.39,0:55:14.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Verse 6 continues, David said: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:14.33,0:55:16.33,Default,,0,0,0,,“I will hand them over.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:16.33,0:55:18.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Who does David hand over? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.33,0:55:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,He hands over, in verse 8, \NRizpah’s two sons, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:24.14,0:55:26.51,Default,,0,0,0,,“the two sons of Rizpah,” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:26.51,0:55:29.81,Default,,0,0,0,,the two people in the whole world \Nthat she loved most. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:29.81,0:55:33.08,Default,,0,0,0,,What a heartbreaking tragedy for Rizpah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:33.08,0:55:35.18,Default,,0,0,0,,but she could do nothing about it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:35.18,0:55:39.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The decision was made; \Nit was out of her control. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:39.45,0:55:42.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Eventually, all seven men are hung. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:42.79,0:55:46.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, under the Mosaic Law, \Nthose executed upon a stake \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:46.76,0:55:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,should have been taken down \Nbefore nightfall and buried. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:50.40,0:55:54.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Burial would have brought closure \Nto this mother’s crushed soul. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:54.77,0:55:56.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And above all, it would conform \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:56.84,0:56:00.87,Default,,0,0,0,,to Jehovah’s requirements \Nfor the dignity of life \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:00.87,0:56:03.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and that proper disposal of the dead body \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:03.71,0:56:06.58,Default,,0,0,0,,would have been according \Nto Jehovah’s instructions. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:06.58,0:56:10.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Undoubtedly, Rizpah knows this, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:10.98,0:56:13.89,Default,,0,0,0,,but it didn’t happen that way. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:13.89,0:56:17.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So can you feel her anguish \Nas night approaches \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:17.69,0:56:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and no one comes to take those bodies down? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:20.96,0:56:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And Rizpah could have been thinking: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:22.96,0:56:26.63,Default,,0,0,0,,‘But the Mosaic Law, \Nno one is following the Law. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:26.63,0:56:28.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s not right.’\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:28.90,0:56:31.27,Default,,0,0,0,,But there was a catch. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:31.27,0:56:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems that the Gibeonites \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:33.44,0:56:37.74,Default,,0,0,0,,were allowed to follow \Na different procedure in this instance \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:37.74,0:56:42.75,Default,,0,0,0,,because a national sin \Nhad been committed by King Saul. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:42.75,0:56:44.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Now did Rizpah know that? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:44.75,0:56:46.75,Default,,0,0,0,,We don’t know. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:46.75,0:56:49.69,Default,,0,0,0,,But what we do know, one day goes by; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:49.69,0:56:51.49,Default,,0,0,0,,the Law is not followed. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:51.49,0:56:53.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The bodies are not taken down. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:53.86,0:56:58.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Two days go by; three days go by. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.67,0:57:00.67,Default,,0,0,0,,What does she do? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:00.67,0:57:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, according to verse 10, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.04,0:57:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Rizpah continues day after day \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:05.44,0:57:08.27,Default,,0,0,0,,in the blaze of that scorching summer sun. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.27,0:57:11.54,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, verse 10 says what she did do. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:11.54,0:57:14.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It says that “she did not allow \Nthe birds of the heavens \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:14.95,0:57:17.45,Default,,0,0,0,,“to land on [those bodies] by day \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:17.45,0:57:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,nor the wild beasts of the field \Nto come near by night.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:21.12,0:57:26.13,Default,,0,0,0,,There she was out there, day after day, \Nshooing those birds away\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:26.13,0:57:31.13,Default,,0,0,0,,—not to draw attention to herself, \Nnot to get justice for her sons, no. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:31.13,0:57:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,She understood, she appreciated, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:34.53,0:57:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and she upheld Jehovah’s view of human life. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:39.34,0:57:43.78,Default,,0,0,0,,She allowed Jehovah’s values \Nto shape her behavior \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:43.78,0:57:46.81,Default,,0,0,0,,even at great personal cost. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:46.81,0:57:49.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You must love this woman. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:49.62,0:57:54.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Although Rizpah probably didn’t understand \Nexactly why things were happening this way\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:54.62,0:57:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,—why was it turning out in this way—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:56.92,0:58:01.16,Default,,0,0,0,,this different procedure \Nof not burying her sons \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:01.16,0:58:05.17,Default,,0,0,0,,had a major impact on her personal life. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:05.17,0:58:09.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet, her conduct showed her love for Jehovah \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:09.77,0:58:13.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and the loyalty that she had \Nfor his arrangements\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:13.21,0:58:17.34,Default,,0,0,0,,—that this love and loyalty \Nburned brightly within her.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.34,0:58:20.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Here’s your big lesson. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:20.01,0:58:26.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, at times, you might feel \Nthat your life is outside of your control. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:26.45,0:58:28.45,Default,,0,0,0,,You may go through a trial \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:28.45,0:58:33.46,Default,,0,0,0,,that allows Jehovah’s standards \Nand decisions to shape you, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:33.46,0:58:37.46,Default,,0,0,0,,perhaps at great personal cost.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:37.46,0:58:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, \Nyou’re familiar with theocratic procedure; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:42.24,0:58:44.47,Default,,0,0,0,,you’re familiar with theocratic policies. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:44.47,0:58:46.47,Default,,0,0,0,,We know that. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:46.47,0:58:50.11,Default,,0,0,0,,But there might come a time \Nwhen an organizational direction\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:50.11,0:58:52.11,Default,,0,0,0,,—an organizational procedure—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:52.11,0:58:57.12,Default,,0,0,0,,is modified for reasons \Nthat you are not fully aware of, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:57.12,0:59:01.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and that decision affects you personally. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:01.96,0:59:03.96,Default,,0,0,0,,What will you do? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:03.96,0:59:08.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Like Rizpah, keep doing what you can \Nunder your circumstances. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:08.29,0:59:10.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Shoo those birds away\N—those negative thoughts. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:10.73,0:59:12.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Stir up that fire.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:12.30,0:59:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t allow your warmth and glow \Nfor Jehovah God to burn out.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:18.24,0:59:20.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, days go by,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:20.87,0:59:24.54,Default,,0,0,0,,according to verse 9 and verse 10: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:24.54,0:59:29.05,Default,,0,0,0,,‘from the start of the harvest to the rain.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:29.05,0:59:32.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Now this implies that this may have been \Nfive to six months \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:32.62,0:59:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,that she kept vigil over her sons’ bodies. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:36.16,0:59:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,What could she have been thinking \Nabout during this time \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:39.19,0:59:42.20,Default,,0,0,0,,that may have been close to half a year? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:42.20,0:59:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What would she have been thinking about? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:45.00,0:59:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,‘How could David be so uncaring \Nas not to command \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:48.80,0:59:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,‘to give my boys a proper burial. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:51.40,0:59:53.51,Default,,0,0,0,,‘And Jehovah,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:53.51,0:59:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,‘after all that I’ve been through,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:56.64,0:59:59.05,Default,,0,0,0,,where are you, Jehovah?’\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:59.05,1:00:02.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Now these might have been \Nnatural thoughts, true. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:02.12,1:00:04.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet, if she did have them, \N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:04.65,1:00:08.35,Default,,0,0,0,,she did not allow these thoughts \Nto put out the fire \N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:08.35,1:00:13.49,Default,,0,0,0,,of her love for God or to make her bitter. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:13.49,1:00:15.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps others even tried \Nto discourage her saying: \N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:15.90,1:00:18.03,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Go home.\NGive up.’\N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:18.03,1:00:20.03,Default,,0,0,0,,But she didn’t. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:20.03,1:00:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Nor did she start a campaign \Nby gathering others to her side. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:24.24,1:00:26.91,Default,,0,0,0,,There’s no record of her bad-mouthing David, \N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:26.91,1:00:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,criticizing his decision as unfair. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:30.24,1:00:33.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Nor did she presume \Nto take the bodies down herself. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:33.15,1:00:36.05,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Well, if nobody is going to do it, \NI’ll do it.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:36.05,1:00:39.45,Default,,0,0,0,,No, in spite of all of these difficulties\N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:39.45,1:00:42.42,Default,,0,0,0,,—imagine—\Nthat Rizpah was suffering, \N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:42.42,1:00:45.29,Default,,0,0,0,,she still had embers of love \N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:45.29,1:00:48.13,Default,,0,0,0,,for Jehovah God glowing brightly \N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:48.13,1:00:51.26,Default,,0,0,0,,that moved her to stay loyal, \N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:51.26,1:00:53.33,Default,,0,0,0,,remain in her place, \N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:53.33,1:00:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and wait on David to make the decision.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:58.27,1:01:03.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Did her faithful endurance really matter? \N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:03.14,1:01:07.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Did anyone notice her plight? \N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:07.21,1:01:09.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Verse 11: \N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:09.88,1:01:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,“David was told\N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:11.88,1:01:16.39,Default,,0,0,0,,what Saul’s concubine Rizpah . . . had done.” \N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:16.39,1:01:18.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So imagine someone goes to David: \N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:18.39,1:01:20.83,Default,,0,0,0,,‘David, there’s this Rizpah; \Nshe’s up there near these bodies. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:20.83,1:01:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,She’s shooing these birds away.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:23.46,1:01:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what did David do? \N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:25.60,1:01:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Did he now, finally, \Ngive Rizpah’s sons a decent burial? \N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:30.60,1:01:34.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, he did more. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:34.74,1:01:37.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Verses 12 through 14 \N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:37.34,1:01:40.35,Default,,0,0,0,,show how David had the bones of Saul \N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:40.35,1:01:43.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and the bones of Jonathan brought \Nall the way from Jabesh-gilead\N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:43.98,1:01:47.65,Default,,0,0,0,,—which might have taken a journey \Nof about 100 miles (160 km)—\N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:47.65,1:01:51.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and buried those bones \Nwith the bones of Rizpah’s sons \N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:51.69,1:01:55.83,Default,,0,0,0,,in Saul’s family plot in Benjamite territory. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:55.83,1:02:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So in the end, \NRizpah got more than she expected. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:01.60,1:02:04.54,Default,,0,0,0,,She saw the bones of her sons \N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:04.54,1:02:07.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and their father buried together. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:07.97,1:02:11.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Rizpah didn’t see that coming, \N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:11.34,1:02:14.05,Default,,0,0,0,,but it was worth the wait.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:14.05,1:02:18.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what’s the big lesson \Nwe want you to remember here? \N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:18.05,1:02:21.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Rizpah’s love and loyalty and endurance \N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:21.09,1:02:24.86,Default,,0,0,0,,provides an example worth imitating. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:24.86,1:02:28.23,Default,,0,0,0,,When you go through a trial, \N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:28.23,1:02:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,remember that others \Nare observing your conduct\N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:31.60,1:02:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,—they’re watching. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:33.60,1:02:36.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And out of frustration, you might feel: \N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:36.10,1:02:40.11,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Well, why haven’t, \Nwhy haven’t the elders done anything? \N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:40.11,1:02:43.58,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Why aren’t the overseers \Ntaking care of this situation? \N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:43.58,1:02:47.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah, why don’t you do something?’ \N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:47.38,1:02:51.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And Jehovah is saying: \N‘I am doing something. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:51.55,1:02:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,‘I’m using your silent example \N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:55.46,1:02:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,‘to show others that \Nwhen you endure a situation, \N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:58.96,1:03:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,‘I will reward them.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:00.89,1:03:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,‘I’ll reward them more than \Nthey ever anticipated, \N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:04.00,1:03:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,‘and it will be worth the wait. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:06.00,1:03:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I, Jehovah, \NI love being a rewarder.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:11.00,1:03:17.88,Default,,0,0,0,,What a noble and honorable way \Nto be used by Jehovah God. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:17.88,1:03:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, Rizpah was not a victim \Nof her circumstances. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:22.38,1:03:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Rather, she became a victor \Nover her adversities. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:28.02,1:03:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The intense heat of her trials \Ndid not break her as a person \N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:31.86,1:03:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,nor crush her desire \Nto please Jehovah God. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:36.80,1:03:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So little is known about her, \N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:40.10,1:03:43.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and yet we learn so much from her. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:43.57,1:03:47.87,Default,,0,0,0,,She never had one spoken word \Nrecorded in the Bible, \N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:47.87,1:03:52.75,Default,,0,0,0,,yet Jehovah must have been very impressed \Nwith this remarkable woman. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:52.75,1:03:57.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Her name and example earned a place \Nin his sacred Book \N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:57.05,1:03:59.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and is worthy of our examination. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:59.15,1:04:01.15,Default,,0,0,0,,She teaches you\N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:01.15,1:04:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,—she teaches you \Nhow to take life’s indignities with dignity. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:07.03,1:04:11.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what helped her endure successfully? \N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:11.23,1:04:15.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps a clue is in her name. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:15.10,1:04:19.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It literally means “Glowing Coal.” \N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:19.37,1:04:22.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we don’t know why \Nshe was given that name, true. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:22.71,1:04:25.75,Default,,0,0,0,,But like a piece of coal \Nglowing warm and bright, \N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:25.75,1:04:30.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Rizpah kept her thoughts focused \Non love for her sons’ loyalty to Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:30.15,1:04:32.15,Default,,0,0,0,,loyalty to his arrangements, \N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:32.15,1:04:36.26,Default,,0,0,0,,confident that relief would eventually come. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:36.26,1:04:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,She was industrious. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:38.26,1:04:42.56,Default,,0,0,0,,She actively guarded her sons’ bodies \Nfrom being eaten by animals. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:42.56,1:04:48.53,Default,,0,0,0,,She didn’t allow negative feelings \Nto shut her down and extinguish her love. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:48.53,1:04:52.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Rather, in the face of what \Nshe might have felt to be an injustice, \N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:52.61,1:04:55.91,Default,,0,0,0,,she did what she could.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:55.91,1:04:57.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what do we want you to remember? \N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:57.91,1:05:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What do we want you to go away with \Nto your assignments thinking about? \N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:03.08,1:05:07.75,Default,,0,0,0,,In the face of a perceived injustice, \Nkeep working; \N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:07.75,1:05:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,keep carrying out \Nyour assigned work assignments; \N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:10.72,1:05:12.26,Default,,0,0,0,,keep doing what you can. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:12.26,1:05:13.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Shoo away those birds. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:13.79,1:05:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Stoke up the fire of your love \Nfor Jehovah God and the brothers. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:18.43,1:05:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And wait on Jehovah \Nto resolve any pending issues, \N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:22.80,1:05:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,confident that relief will come now \Nor in the new world. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:27.67,1:05:30.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It will be worth that wait. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:30.74,1:05:36.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And yet, above all, above all, be a Rizpah. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:36.42,1:05:38.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Under all circumstances, \N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:38.52,1:05:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,keep your love for God \Nburning brightly like a glowing coal.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:48.83,1:05:53.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Those talks were inspiring \Nto the students of the 143rd class, \N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:53.83,1:05:57.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and I am sure that you feel much \Nthe same way after viewing them. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:57.94,1:06:01.67,Default,,0,0,0,,But you probably are wondering, \N‘What about the rest of the program?’\N
Dialogue: 0,1:06:01.67,1:06:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Wonder no longer. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:06:03.48,1:06:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Part 2 and Part 3 will be posted \Non the Video on Demand section \N
Dialogue: 0,1:06:08.15,1:06:11.02,Default,,0,0,0,,of JW Broadcasting later this month. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:06:11.02,1:06:15.99,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, Part 2 is a video entitled\NThe Inside Story.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:06:15.99,1:06:19.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It is scheduled to be posted\Nnext Monday, December 11.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:06:19.49,1:06:23.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You will enjoy hearing experiences \Nfrom some of the graduates of the class.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:06:23.86,1:06:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Until the next monthly program, \Nthis is JW Broadcasting \N
Dialogue: 0,1:06:27.80,1:06:30.82,Default,,0,0,0,,coming to you from the world headquarters \Nof Jehovah’s Witnesses.\N
